HEADWORD: Sweeper
<hw>Sweep"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, sweeps, or cleans by sweeping; a sweep; <as>as, a carpet
<ex>sweeper</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is oxygen which is the great <qex>sweeper</qex> of the
economy.</q> <rj><qau>Huxley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweeping</ent>⟦br⟧
